Organics:

She nerviously chuckled as she walked out of the quarters towards the 
mess hall.  SHe found a booster seat and set Elita in it.  SHe then 
found a menu of some sorts, that had some pictures of the food in 
it.  She showed the menu to the baby, hoping she would be able to 
choose something.
"Here, you pick out what you want, and I will get you some to eat.  
You can have as much as you want, and then we can go play a game.  
Okay?"



--- In nbwrpg@yahoogroups.com, "airly2000" <airly2002@h...> wrote:
Elita:
 
Elita looked to Organics and whined, her hunger was increasing.
 
--- In nbwrpg@yahoogroups.com, robert riley <bustercross365@y...> 
wrote:
Malice/ Organics:
  
"It sounds like you're awfully hunger.  Tell you what: if you go 
with Organics, she'll get you whatever you want to eat.  How's that?"
Organics stepped right up to Malice and Elita, smiling big.
"C'mon, we can go eat, then go play games, ok?"
Malice seized the opportunity.  He gently put Elita right into 
Organics' waiting arms.
"I'm sure she won't do anything crazy Elita, I hope."
He patted the baby on the shoulder, then his sister, then walked 
down the hall to the labs.  He ounded a corner and found Wolfblade 
at work.  He stepped behind her, leaned over her, and rested his 
hands on the bench in front of her.  He looked at her now upside 
down face, a big grin on his face.
"Parents don't take care of children all the time.  They hire 
babysitters!"
